---

<SessionPage
  title="Session 7 · .NET: request model validation"
  heading="Follow one request from JSON body to runtime validation"
  lede="Read a supplied Minimal API boundary, separate C# nullability guidance from an actual runtime rule, and predict two responses. No project construction is required."
  backHref="/topics/dotnet/"
  backLabel=".NET sessions"
>
  <SessionSection title="The path through this endpoint">
    <p><code>JSON request body → ShippingAddress address → handler check → HTTP response</code></p>
    <p>For this endpoint, ASP.NET Core creates a <code>ShippingAddress</code> value from the JSON request body and passes it into the handler as <code>address</code>. The positional record gives that request data three named public properties.</p>
  </SessionSection>

  <SessionSection title="One distinction: annotation versus runtime rule">
    <Callout>
      <code>string Street</code> tells C# tooling that this property is intended to be non-null. It does not make blank text such as <code>"   "</code> invalid by itself. The executable <code>string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(...)</code> check enforces that boundary rule at runtime.
    </Callout>
    <p>This lesson uses a whitespace-only value deliberately. Every JSON property is present, so you can focus on the validation branch rather than missing-body or serializer behaviour.</p>
  </SessionSection>

  <SessionSection title="Supplied record and endpoint">
    <Code code={endpointCode} lang="csharp" />
    <ul>
      <li>If <code>Street</code> is null, empty, or only whitespace, the first return ends the handler with <code>BadRequest</code>.</li>
      <li>Otherwise execution reaches <code>Ok</code>.</li>
      <li>The record carries request-shaped data; it does not validate itself.</li>
    </ul>
  </SessionSection>

  <SessionSection title="The two request bodies">
    <p><strong>Request 1: ordinary street value</strong></p>
    <Code code={validBody} lang="json" />
    <p><strong>Request 2: whitespace-only street value</strong></p>
    <Code code={blankBody} lang="json" />
  </SessionSection>

  <ReplyTask id="learn:dotnet/007:q1" copyText={replyText} difficulty={3}>
    <p>Without running the code, answer four compact questions:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Which handler parameter receives the body data, and what is its type?</li>
      <li>Does non-nullable <code>string</code> itself reject whitespace at runtime? Name the expression that performs the check.</li>
      <li>For Request 1, predict the HTTP status and returned JSON values.</li>
      <li>For Request 2, predict the HTTP status and returned JSON values.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Exact JSON spacing and property order do not matter.</p>
  </ReplyTask>
</SessionPage>
